the incumbent will be responsible for integrating expertise from across bmofg, and externally as required, to design, develop and implement the small business segment strategy and driving the profitable growth and retention of small business customers.  
key accountabilities
strategic planning


participate in integrated cross-functional teams to provide enhanced understanding of business issues through strategy-focused operational intelligence, analysis and facilitation for both the planning and implementation of strategic initiatives;

support business leadership in the development of the annual strategic planning by doing analysis and preparing presentations;

conduct scenario planning and build business cases to support strategic options;

disaggregate strategic problems into relevant issues and develop appropriate analytical approaches to support the design of the strategic project/program;

consider the “big picture” when assessing whether or not a course of action is advisable in terms of the group and enterprise goals;

explain complex problems situations or business opportunities through innovative presentations so that all parts of the strategic project/program are more readily understood;

conduct key analytics required to inform strategic recommendations; develop insights and recommendations that are actionable in alignment with project/program goals;

make proposal to leadership based on facts and gain approval to proceed with strategic planning;

socialize strategic options with key stakeholders to gain support for proposal;

build implementation plans and define tactics and strategies to ensure successful business results; and 

engage and communicate with stakeholders on an ongoing basis and ensure changing resource and project requirements are met and understood andto ensure the successful completion of project deliverables.
project/program execution


lead the implementation of strategic initiatives within group and across bmo overall by partnering with appropriate senior managers/directors; complexities of initiatives may be high and usually involve multiple stakeholders across the enterprise;

scope of initiatives include people, processes, tools and technology;

ensure projects/programs are delivered on scope, time and budget;

manage multiple programs/projects simultaneously and resolve conflicting priorities and objectives;

prepare project plans and keep key stakeholders informed of the process and progress;

effectively communicate key messages/recommendations/results to all managerial levels;

identify enablers and key issues prior to and during implementation, raise issues with key stakeholders and offer solutions to resolve issues or risks that jeopardize project/program delivery;

prepare communications to help launch and support initiatives and contribute to training support; and

partner with stakeholders to ensure effective change management plans are in place to support initiatives.
 
monitoring & reporting


proactively identify opportunities to enhance reporting to elevate insights for all stakeholders;

support tracking of program results and identify trends and insights;

utilize and create reporting analysis to identify areas for growth and product innovation; and

use data to understand the trends for the business results and raise any issues with adoption, migration, etc… depending on the project/program
 
relationship management 


act as the main relationship management for multiple stakeholders (internal and external) for assigned programs and projects;

establish working relationships with key managers within business groups and other corporate areas; and 

partner with other areas of the organization and/or external vendors/contracts as required to facilitate the achievement of deliverables and overall objectives.
 
risk management & control


follow all appropriate risk management and project/program guidelines to mitigate the risk of project/program failure

ensure project issues and risks are identified, quantified, managed and tracked.  ensure risks, assumptions and constraints are appropriately communicated and escalated when necessary.qualifications knowledge & skills
knowledge:
·     proven track record and experience in development and delivery of strategic initiatives impacting people, processes and technology;
·     expert knowledge of the financial industry (minimum 10 years experience);
·     commercial and small business banking experience an asset;
·      strong financial acumen;
·     university degree is essential; mba desirable (or other applicable advanced degree/certification);
·     proven track record and experience in development and delivery of strategic initiatives impacting people, processes and technology;
·      in-depth knowledge  proficiency in excel, powerpoint and microsoft suite skills is a must;
·     proven track record delivering innovative solutions from concept to change management; and
·     demonstrated ability to lead large programs in a complex matrixed environment.
 
skills:
·     expert consulting, strategic thinking capability , project management and, change management;
·     proven ability to implement strategic vision;
·     proficiency in excel, powerpoint and microsoft suite skills is a must;
·     expert leadership capabilities;
·     proven collaboration and stakeholder management skills;
·     in-depth interpersonal skills;
·     expert ability to navigate the corporate environment to deliver results;
·     working impact and influence capabilities; and 
·      results oriented and is able to work under minimal direction.
we’re here to help at bmo we have a shared purpose; we put the customer at the centre of everything we do – helping people is in our dna. for 200 years we have thought about the future—the future of our customers, our communities and our people. we help our customers and our communities by working together, innovating and pushing boundaries to bring them our very best every day. together we’re changing the way people think about a bank. 
 
as a member of the bmo team you are valued, respected and heard, and you have more ways to grow and make an impact. we strive to help you make an impact from day one – for yourself and our customers. we’ll support you with the tools and resources you need to reach new milestones, as you help our customers reach theirs. from in-depth training and coaching, to manager support and network-building opportunities, we’ll help you gain valuable experience, and broaden your skillset. to find out more visit us at https://bmocareers.com. 
bmo is committed to an inclusive, equitable and accessible workplace. by learning from each other’s differences, we gain strength through our people and our perspectives. accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process.
 
